        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 4:44PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 444 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles southwest of Forest City, or 6 miles northwest of Chesnee,
moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Harris and Fingerville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
